          "type": "html",
          "name": "question10",
          "html": "<ol style=\"list-style-type: decimal;margin-left:26px;\">\n    <li><span style='line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-size:10.0pt;'>Use of Allen&apos;s test to demonstrate adequate collateral flow</span></li>\n    <li><span style='line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-size:10.0pt;'>Incision based on anatomical landmarks that are explicitly defined</span></li>\n    <li><span style='line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-size:10.0pt;'>Mobilisation of the radial artery using blunt and sharp dissection avoiding damage to surrounding structures</span></li>\n    <li><span style='line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-size:10.0pt;'>Safe ligation of branches of radial artery</span></li>\n    <li><span style='line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-size:10.0pt;'>Safe ligation of artery proximally and distally</span></li>\n    <li><span style='line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-size:10.0pt;'>Stores artery safely for later use</span></li>\n    <li><span style='line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-size:10.0pt;'>Haemostasis</span></li>\n    <li><span style='line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;font-size:10.0pt;'>Aesthetic closure of skin and subcutaneous tissues</span></li>\n</ol>"
         }
